com.google.api.gax.core

Interface Page<RequestT,ResponseT,ResourceT>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<ResourceT>

    public interface Page<RequestT,ResponseT,ResourceT>
extends Iterable<ResourceT>
    A Page object wraps an API list method response.

    Callers can iterate over the Page object to get all elements returned in the page. The Page object also provides methods to retrieve additional pages using the page token, and to get the API request and response objects.

      • hasNextPage

        boolean hasNextPage()
        Returns true if there are more pages that can be retrieved from the API.

      • getNextPageToken

        Returns the next page token from the response.

      • getNextPage

        Page<RequestT,ResponseT,ResourceT> getNextPage()
        Retrieves the next Page object using the next page token. If there are no more pages to be retrieved, a NoSuchElementException is thrown. The hasNextPage() method should be used to check if a Page object is available.

      • getNextPage

        Page<RequestT,ResponseT,ResourceT> getNextPage(int pageSize)
        Retrieves the next Page object using the next page token. Uses the pageSize argument to set the page size parameter for the next page request. If there are no more pages to be retrieved, a NoSuchElementException is thrown. The hasNextPage() method should be used to check if a Page object is available.

      • getPageElementCount

        int getPageElementCount()
        Return the number of elements in the response.

      • iteratePages

        Iterable<Page<RequestT,ResponseT,ResourceT>> iteratePages()
        Return an iterator over Page objects, beginning with this object. Additional Page objects are retrieved lazily via API calls until all elements have been retrieved.

      • getRequestObject

        RequestT getRequestObject()
        Gets the request object used to generate the Page.

      • getResponseObject

        ResponseT getResponseObject()
        Gets the API response object.
